<style>
    .credit {
        font-size: .8em;
        text-align: center;
    }    
</style>
<p>
    A riddling ancient treatise wrote,     
    <blockquote>
        I think a number, unknown to you.
        
        If you count by threes, there is a remainder 2.
        If you count by fives, there is a remainder 3.
        If you count by sevens, there is remainder 2.
        
        Could you tell what my number is ?
    </blockquote>
</p>
<div>
<img src="421px-Sun_Zi_Suanjing.jpg" style="width: 20%;">
    <div class="credit">
    <span>Source: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sun_Tzu_(mathematician)">wikipedia</a></span>
    </div>
</div>
<p><strong>Input data: </strong>a list of tuples, whose tuple contains <strong>remainder and its divisor</strong></p>
<p><strong>Output data: </strong>The output will be a number, <strong>the smallest possible natural number</strong>.</p>
<div class="for_info_only">
    <p>
        <strong>Example:</strong>
    </p>
    <pre class="brush: python">
assert( checkio( [ (2,3), (3,5), (2,7) ] ) == 23 ), "First Test"
assert( checkio( [ (1,5), (4,7) ] ) == 11 ), "Second Test"
assert( checkio( [ (1,3), (2,5), (3,7) ] ) == 52 ), "Third Test"
assert( checkio( [ (1,2), (1,3), (1,5) ] ) == 1 ), "Fourth Test"
assert( checkio( [ (2,4), (7,9) ] ) == 34 ), "Fifth Test"
    </pre>
</div>
